'''Chris Wade''' is an English born{{clarify|date=December 2019}} writer, musician and filmmaker. He runs the music project [[Dodson and Fogg]]. Dodson and Fogg {{clarify span|text=has had BBC airplay|date=December 2019}} <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/b8f7130d-80bc-485e-b895-ace6aab99775|title=Dodson and Fogg - New Songs, Playlists & Latest News - BBC Music|website=BBC|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref> and received positive reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pennyblackmusic.co.uk/MagSitePages/Review/11237/Dodson-and-Fogg-Phantom-Gesture-CD-on-Wisdom-Twin-Records/|title=Dodson and Fogg: Phantom Gesture (CD on Wisdom Twin Records)|website=www.pennyblackmusic.co.uk|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://getreadytorock.me.uk/blog/tag/chris-wade/|title=Chris Wade - Get Ready to ROCK! News - Reviews - Interviews - RadioGet Ready to ROCK! News - Reviews - Interviews - Radio|website=Get Ready to ROCK! News - Reviews - Interviews - Radio|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elsewhere.co.nz/absoluteelsewhere/8756/dodson-and-fogg-revisited-again-2019-through-the-english-countryside-to-dark-and-light/|title=DODSON AND FOGG. REVISITED. AGAIN (2019): Through the English countryside to dark and light . . .|website=Elsewhere by Graham Reid|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref> He also writes fiction and non fiction books.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beefheart.com/the-music-of-captain-beefheart-by-chris-wade/|title=The Music of Captain Beefheart by Chris Wade – Captain Beefheart Radar Station|website=www.beefheart.com|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://magazine.brighton.co.uk/Brighton-Music/News/Review-Chris-Wades-Comprehensive-Woody-Allen-On-Screen-Overview-/42_120_4784|title=Brighton Magazine - Review: Chris Wade's Comprehensive Woody Allen On Screen Overview|website=Magazine.brighton.co.uk|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://neilyoungnews.thrasherswheat.org/2016/08/review-contest-music-of-neil-young-by.html|title=Neil Young News: REVIEW + CONTEST: The Music of Neil Young by Chris Wade|publisher=|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref> He worked with [[Rik Mayall]] on his ''Cutey and the Sofaguard'' audiobook, which Mayall narrated,<ref>://www.comedy.co.uk/people/rik_mayall/shop/4400/cutey_and_the_sofaguard_audio/</ref><ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p020b2wf</ref> and runs ''Hound Dawg Magazine'', for which he has interviewed such people as [[Donovan]], [[Sharon Stone]] and many others. Wade also makes documentaries, such as ''George Melly: The Certainty of Hazard''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thestrangebrew.co.uk/george-melly-documentary-film/|title=George Melly documentary film|date=8 August 2018|publisher=|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref> and ''The Immortal Orson Welles'', the latter which premiered on [[Talking Pictures TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/TalkingPicturesTV/posts/1573644799436170|title=Talking Pictures TV Sky 328 Freeview 81 Freesat 306 Virgin 445|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wellesnet.com/immortal-orson-welles-documentary/|title='The Immortal Orson Welles' documentary looks at later work • Wellesnet - Orson Welles Web Resource|date=26 January 2019|publisher=|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref><ref>https://www.renownfilms.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/RenownNewsletterApril.pdf</ref> His art film, ''The Apple Picker'', won Best Film at Sydney's World Film Festival in 2017 and featured singer and actress [[Toyah Willcox]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://toyahwillcox.com/the-apple-picker-a-chris-wade-film/|title=THE APPLE PICKER, A CHRIS WADE FILM — TOYAH|publisher=|accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref>

